The transported scalar φ is the local oxygen concentration (vol.%), which is also the product of the oxygen solubility α and the local oxygen partial pressure (pO2) according to Henry’s Law (φ = α*pO2). Oxygen solubility α is 3.1385 × 10−5 ml O2/mmHg*ml fluid in culture medium and 2.855 × 10−5 ml O2/mmHg*ml fluid in plasma. D is the oxygen diffusion coefficient, which is 2.92 × 10−9 m2/s in culture medium and 2.18 × 10−9 m2/s in plasma.2,17,33,44 Oxygen consumption by the primary porcine hepatocytes in the AMC-BAL was modeled by an additional source term Sφ, which was only implemented in regions that were designated to contain hepatocytes. 2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
